sentences: Ryan Santiago (born May 25, 1994), known professionally as Royal & the Serpent, is an American singer and songwriter.
A New Jersey native, Ryan Santiago was born on May 25, 1994.
In 2017, Santiago independently released "Temperance", her debut single under the stage name Royal & the Serpent.
In 2018, she released her second single, "Together", and was featured on the song "Wicked" by music producer Tommee Profitt.
"Overwhelmed", Royal & the Serpent's first single on Atlantic, was released in June 2020, and her debut EP Get a Grip was released in October.
Royal & the Serpent's second EP Searching for Nirvana was released in June 2021.
Santiago took up competitive dance as a child, until she "shattered both [her] heel plates" after jumping off a stage while performing when she was 14 years old.
In her teenage years, Santiago learned how to play the guitar and began writing songs.
By the end of 2019, she had signed with Atlantic Records.
"Overwhelmed", Royal & the Serpent's first single on Atlantic, was released in June 2020, and her debut EP Get a Grip was released in October.
That year, she joined English singer Yungblud's Weird Time of Life virtual tour as a supporting act.
